OL,3,CLabour to reform Ofgem to give more
OL,4,Cprotections after energy bills crisis
OL,6,FEnergy Consumers Minister Miatta
OL,7,FFahnbulleh said the government has
OL,8,F"learned from the energy crisis" and
OL,9,Fadded, "bills are still too high".
OL,11,FFahnbulleh said: "We will ensure that
OL,12,Fworking people have access to the best
OL,13,Fpossible support to choose more
OL,14,Faffordable, smarter, clean energy that
OL,15,Fis right for them."
OL,17,FShe said the review of Ofgem would
OL,18,Falso "set it up for the transition to
OL,19,Fnet zero".
