OL,3,CLabour to reform Ofgem to give more
OL,4,Cprotections after energy bills crisis
OL,6,FIn November Ofgem announced the energy
OL,7,Fprice cap would rise by 1.2% in
OL,8,FJanuary, the second in a matter of
OL,9,Fmonths after a 10% hike was announced
OL,10,Fin October.
OL,12,FOfgem changes the price cap for
OL,13,Fhouseholds every three months, largely
OL,14,Fbased on the cost of energy on
OL,15,Fwholesale markets.
OL,17,FAlthough down from their peak in 2022,
OL,18,Fenergy bills are still at very high
OL,19,Flevels when compared to the previous
OL,20,F10 years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
